[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'There is a new open-source tool that was released just over the weekend. It\'s called OmniAgent, and we\'re going to unpack this today because it is a very powerful and free-to-use meta harness. A meta harness is a tool that allows you to run longer AI coding workflows mixing'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'AI coding assistants. And so, the most classic example that people really like right now is using Claude Code for the implementation in a workflow, and then reviewing that code with Codex. All of the top engineers right now, they\'re not'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'relying on a single model or even a single harness for their workflows anymore because we want to lean on the different strengths of the different AI coding assistants, and also have these different sessions for the sake of'

[00:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'context and token optimization, which is more important than ever right now. And OmniAgent is the layer above the AI coding assistant that makes this orchestration really straightforward because if we don\'t have a tool like'

[00:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this, just one session to manage all of our coding agents, and we can build custom agents. We\'ll get into all of this here. If we don\'t have something like this, we have to go between different terminals, create all these handoff documents. It really isn\'t straightforward. And so, the idea of a'

[01:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'meta harness, it really is peak harness engineering. And so, I want to talk about why meta harnesses are so important right now. Then we\'ll get into how easy it is to use OmniAgent to drive our AI coding workflows, even building a'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'custom setup in the platform. Cool. So, let\'s start off by talking about why meta harnesses are so important right now. And so, first things first, if there\'s one lesson we can learn this year for AI coding, it\'s that the'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'harness matters as much as or maybe even more than the model. And that\'s even more apparent right now with the recent ban of Fable 5. We can\'t even rely on having the best LLMs for our AI coding workflows or getting better ones. And'

[01:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'so, if we want to make our AI coding more reliable, that brings us back to the harness. If the LLM can\'t get better, then we better make the system around the LLM more powerful. So, your harness is everything like your system'

[01:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prompt, tools, skills, workflows, rules, all of that together packaged up is our harness for making a single AI coding assistant more reliable for us. And the meta harness, this is what a lot of'

[02:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'people are really starting to lean into right now. This is the next big thing for AI coding. Instead of making one coding agent better, what if we have the layer above that orchestrates many AI coding assistants working together on a'

